<p><em>"The best chance we have to avoid becoming a totalitarian state is that the state itself would likely become so large that it would simply collapse under it's own weight. It would likely be too ambitious, too large and too cumbersome. It would eventually consume all the resources of the economy while producing nothing in return, and the system could not survive. It is not sustainable." <br /></em></p>
